or_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;1\/1&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][nectar_highlighted_text style=&#8221;none&#8221; custom_font_size=&#8221;3vw&#8221; font_size_tablet=&#8221;6vw&#8221; font_line_height=&#8221;1.2&#8243; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]\n<h1>Frequently Asked Questions<\/h1>\n[\/nectar_highlighted_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row type=&#8221;full_width_content&#8221; full_screen_row_position=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;custom&#8221; column_margin_custom=&#8221;7vw&#8221; equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;top&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_color=&#8221;#f8f8f8&#8243; scene_position=&#8221;center&#8221; top_padding=&#8221;3%&#8221; bottom_padding=&#8221;6%&#8221; left_padding_desktop=&#8221;7vw&#8221; constrain_group_2=&#8221;yes&#8221; right_padding_desktop=&#8221;7vw&#8221; text_color=&#8221;dark&#8221; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; row_border_radius_applies=&#8221;bg&#8221; row_position_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; row_position_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; row_position_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.8&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; shape_divider_color=&#8221;#000000&#8243; shape_divider_position=&#8221;bottom&#8221; shape_divider_height=&#8221;99%&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; shape_type=&#8221;straight_section&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][vc_column left_padding_desktop=&#8221;2vw&#8221; flex_gap_desktop=&#8221;10px&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; column_position=&#8221;default&#8221; advanced_gradient_angle=&#8221;0&#8243; gradient_direction=&#8221;left_to_right&#8221; overlay_strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221; column_padding_type=&#8221;advanced&#8221; gradient_type=&#8221;default&#8221;][toggles style=&#8221;minimal_shadow&#8221; accordion=&#8221;true&#8221; accordion_starting_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221;][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;h3&#8243; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What is the Custom Occupation Report?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The Custom Occupation Report allows migration professionals to generate a detailed, professional-grade report for any occupation in the ANZSCO catalogue. You can choose which sections and visa pathways to include:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Skilled visas<\/strong> (Subclass 189, 190, 491)<\/li>\n<li><strong data-start=\"394\" data-end=\"440\">State and Territory nomination eligibility<\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong>Employer-Sponsored visas<\/strong> (subclass 482, 186, 494)<\/li>\n<li><strong>DAMA Eligibility<\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong>Graduate visa<\/strong> (subclass 485)<\/li>\n<li><strong>Visa Eligibility Summary<\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong>Backlog Overview <\/strong>(SkillSelect EOIs)<\/li>\n<li><strong>ANZSCO Information Sheet<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Each report is generated as a branded, ready-to-share PDF for your clients.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Who can use the Custom Occupation Report?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]This tool is designed for registered migration agents, Australian legal practitioners, and migration professionals who require accurate, branded client documentation.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;h3&#8243; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What\u2019s included in the report?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]Anzscosearch offers a <strong>Tailored Report<\/strong> built around specific client scenarios. A flexible format where each report can include any combination of the following sections:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eligibility Summary Report<\/strong>: A concise summary showing: <strong>ANZSCO eligibility <\/strong>across Skilled (189, 190, 491), Employer-Sponsored (482, 186, 494) and Graduate (485) pathways. Ideal for a quick, professional summary combining eligibility and occupation details in one document.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Visa Requirements (Overview &amp; Key Criteria) and ANZSCO Eligibility\u00a0<\/strong>\u2013 concise pages outlining how each program works and the headline criteria:<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Skilled (Points-tested): age threshold, occupation on the relevant list, positive skills assessment, Competent English, points score met at invitation, and invitation required; plus, the key differences between 189\/190\/491.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>State \/ Territory Eligibility. Nomination pathways by state or territory.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Employer-Sponsored: nomination fundamentals (genuine full-time role, eligible occupation), AMSR and minimum salary thresholds (e.g. TSMIT\/CSIT\/SSIT), and LMT where required; plus, streams (482, 186, 494) and when skills assessment or \u201cCompetent\/Vocational English\u201d apply.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Designated Area Migration Agreement (DAMA) eligibility.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<ul>\n<li>Graduate (485): streams (Post-Vocational and Post-Higher Education), core settings (age, English benchmark, when a skills assessment is required), and the Australian Study Requirement elements.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Professional Advice<\/strong> \u2013 a dedicated space to add your own comments\/recommendations (or leave it blank).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Backlog Overview<\/strong> \u2013 a snapshot of current SkillSelect EOIs by points band and status (Submitted, Invited, Lodged), providing a clear view of competition and invitation pressure for the nominated occupation.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ANZSCO Information Sheet\u00a0<\/strong>\u2013 occupation description, tasks, assessing authority, indicative skill level, and any listed specialisations.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Does the report include State and Territory nomination eligibility and criteria?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The report includes a <strong>high-level overview of State and Territory nomination eligibility<\/strong>, showing whether an occupation is listed for nomination and which pathways or streams may apply across each jurisdiction.<\/p>\n<p>However, <strong>detailed State and Territory nomination criteria and requirements are not included<\/strong>. These requirements are extensive, frequently updated, and vary significantly between jurisdictions and pathways. Including full criteria for every State and Territory would substantially increase the length and complexity of the report and undermine its purpose of providing a clear, client-friendly summary.<\/p>\n<p>To ensure accuracy, the report <strong>includes links to the official State and Territory websites<\/strong>, allowing users to\u00a0<strong>access the most current nomination requirements<\/strong> directly from the original sources.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;How long is the report?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The length of each report depends on the sections you select. A simple ANZSCO Information Sheet is usually <strong>4\u20135 pages<\/strong>, while a fully customised report that includes all visa pathways and sections can extend to around <strong>20\u201322 pages<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>The final length may also vary depending on whether you include professional advice or comments. The Professional Advice section allows up to <strong>1,000 words<\/strong> (around 6,500 characters) \u2014 roughly two pages of written input. The entire report is designed to remain concise and well-structured, providing clients with essential information in a clear, easy-to-read format.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Can I include my own disclaimer or terms in the report?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]Yes. You can add your firm\u2019s or business disclaimer text in the <em>Professional Advice<\/em> section, ensuring it aligns with your professional standards and compliance obligations.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Is this report considered immigration advice?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The report compiles factual migration information from official sources. Any advice or commentary added within the <em>Professional Advice<\/em> section represents the subscriber\u2019s professional input. This structure helps you provide tailored advice within a compliant, consistent framework.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;h3&#8243; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Can I brand the report with my logo or business name?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]Yes. Subscribers can upload their logo and business details, which appear on every report \u2014 presenting it as a professional document prepared by your practice.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Will my clients be able to see that the report was generated through Anzscosearch?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]No. Reports are fully <strong>white-labelled<\/strong> for professional use.<\/p>\n<p>Anzscosearch\u2019s branding does not appear anywhere \u2014 only your logo and business details are displayed, making the report look entirely like your own.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What makes this different from a standard occupation search?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]The Customised Occupation Report transforms raw search results into a structured, professional-grade document. It brings together data from multiple Anzscosearch tools and official government sources, applies the latest migration settings, and presents everything in a clear, branded format.<\/p>\n<p>Unlike a standard occupation search, this tool lets you customise what\u2019s included, add your professional insights, and generate a polished, client-ready PDF \u2014 all in one step.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Accent-Color&#8221; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;Can I cancel or change my plan at any time?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]Yes. You can upgrade, downgrade, or cancel your subscription at any time. Access to the report feature will remain active until the end of your billing period.[\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][\/toggles][\/vc_column][vc_column right_padding_desktop=&#8221;2vw&#8221; top_margin_tablet=&#8221;10%&#8221; flex_gap_desktop=&#8221;10px&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;none&#8221; column_link_target=&#82